- label: --json create, --json set, --json unset, --json rm, --json link, and --json unlink mutations with multiple matching Hooks run matching Hooks sequentially after commit; when one or more earlier Hooks succeed and a later Hook fails or times out, the mutation remains committed, the successful and failing or timed-out Hook Runs persist, later matching Hooks do not run, stdout stays empty, and stderr reports the committed Hook failure or timeout
  id: 9ev
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh json_multiple_matching_hooks_stop_after_failure_or_timeout
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Plain create, --json rm, plain link, --json unlink, plain single-field set, --json single-field unset, plain multi-field set, and --json multi-field unset mutations whose matching Hook fails after commit still invoke the Hook with stable AGENT_STORE_EVENT, AGENT_STORE_ID, and AGENT_STORE_KIND; create, rm, and multi-field record mutations omit misleading link or single-field env, link mutations include relation/target env, single-field record mutations include field key/value old/new env with spaces, equals signs, quotes, backslashes, and newlines preserved for hook consumers, stdout remains empty, and the Store mutation and Hook Run persist
  id: 06p
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_failure_preserves_link_context_env
